## Overview

This is a [Home Assistant](https://www.home-assistant.io/) configuration repository for a smart home hub running HA 2025.8.3. Configuration is written in YAML. There are no build steps or tests тАФ changes take effect when loaded by the running Home Assistant instance.

## Key Configuration Files

- `configuration.yaml` тАФ Main HA config. Defines integrations (MQTT, emulated Hue, HTTP proxy trust), template covers, input helpers, and timers. All other YAML files are included from here.
- `automations.yaml` тАФ Automation rules (loaded via `automation: !include`)
- `scripts.yaml` тАФ Reusable scripts (loaded via `script: !include`)
- `scenes.yaml` тАФ Scene definitions (currently empty)
- `customize.yaml` тАФ Entity attribute overrides
- `secrets.yaml` тАФ Sensitive values referenced via `!secret` in other files

## Architecture: Garage Door Control

The primary automation domain is a **safe garage door controller** built around a Shelly1 MQTT relay (`shellies/shelly1-113C9D`):

- **Hardware**: Shelly1 relay sends MQTT pulse to trigger the physical door motor
- **Template cover** (`cover.garage_door_safe`): A virtual cover entity that adds safety logic on top of the raw MQTT sensor/relay
- **Safety mechanism**: An `input_boolean.garage_motion_lock` prevents operation during active motion. A `timer.garage_travel_delay` tracks door travel time.
- **Scripts**: `garage_open`, `garage_close`, `garage_stop`, `garage_pulse`, `garage_force_unlock` тАФ the open/close scripts check lock state, pulse the relay, then start the travel timer
- **Automations**: Manage lock state transitions (unlock on timer end, unlock when fully open, cancel timer on manual unlock, auto-disable 10-min override)

